title: 'Virat needs to dictate terms, not anchor, at T20 WC'

description: India condemns Pakistan's 'dubious track record' while slamming the remarks made by Islamabad's envoy on Kashmir in the UN General Assembly. India's response came after Pakistan's UN envoy Munir Akram made negative remarks against New Delhi, including references to Kashmir, CAA and Ram temple in Ayodhya during his address in a UNGA meeting on 'Culture of Peace.'
title: 'Most dubious track record': India slams Pak over remarks at UN

description: Chinese nationals in the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP) region are now subject to movement restrictions. The KP government has decreed that Chinese citizens must be accompanied by armored vehicles when traveling in the area. This instruction was issued by a senior police official during a meeting held on Wednesday.
title: Security measures tightened for Chinese nationals in Pakistan

description: Police have arrested more than 2,000 people during pro-Palestinian protests at college campuses across the United States in recent weeks. Demonstrations — and arrests — have occurred in almost every corner of the nation. But in the last 24 hours, they’ve drawn the most attention at the University of California, Los Angeles.
title: Pro-Palestinian protests: Police arrest over 2,300 protesters

description: Rahul Gandhi accuses Prajwal Revanna of raping 400 women, endorsed by PM Modi. Alleges BJP's anti-women stance. Demands an apology and criticizes BJP govt for inaction. Robert Vadra echoes concerns about Prajwal's escape abroad.
title: Karnataka sex tapes: 'Prajwal Revanna raped 400 women'

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, surged in trade on Friday. While BSE Sensex rose over 400 points to cross the 75,000 mark, Nifty50 was above 22,750.
title: Sensex surges over 400 points to cross 75,000

description: BJP on Thursday had declared Dinesh Pratap Singh as its nominee for Rae Bareli, a constituency where he previously faced off against Sonia Gandhi in the 2019 Lok Sabha elections and was defeated by a margin of nearly 1.6 lakh votes. He, however, received a total of 38 percent votes, the highest number of votes among all BJP candidates in the history of Rae Bareli.
title: Lok Sabha polls: Meet Rahul Gandhi's challenger in Rae Bareli

description: 25th anniversary of Kargil war, Indian Army's ‘Operation Vijay’, marked by epic battles. Lieutenant Colonel Sada S Peter shared untold stories. Kargil victory celebrated in Delhi.
title: A commander recollects his days and nights at Kargil war

description: Congress on Friday declared its candidates for Amethi and Rae Bareli Lok Sabha constituencies of Uttar Pradesh.  Rahul Gandhi has been fielded from Rae Bareli while Kishori Lal Sharma will be contesting from Amethi. Kishori Lal Sharma will be in the fray against BJP's Smriti Irani, who defeated Rahul Gandhi in the 2019 Lok Sabha elections.
title: All you need to know about KL Sharma, Congress's Amethi candidate

description: Ajit Agarkar's had to take a tough call on Rinku Singh's T20 exclusion due to experience preference amid public outcry. Squad decisions based on team combinations, conditions uncertainty, and needed skills for the World Cup. Despite calls for introducing fresh blood in India's T20 team, the selectors chose to go with experience yet again.
title: 'Leaving Rinku Singh out of team was the toughest decision'

description: Virat has touched the 500-run mark in this IPL, showcasing a remarkable performance with a century and four half-centuries, while maintaining a commendable strike rate of 147.49, which certainly cannot be deemed as subpar.  The T20 World Cup, jointly hosted by West Indies and USA, will see India facing Ireland, Pakistan, Canada and USA in the initial group stage.
title: 'Never doubt Virat Kohli, he is a World Cup player'

description: Vijaya Deepika Gangapatnam, battling Brittle Bone Disease, achieves success in table tennis despite numerous fractures. With dreams of Paralympics, she navigates challenges with family support and determination, showcasing resilience and talent in the sport. She was the youngest to win a medal at the UTT Para Table Tennis National Championship in Indore this March. In fact, the Secunderabad girl clinched silver in singles and bronze in doubles.
title: 13-year-old defies 45 fractures, fate to script dream TT tale

description: India's T20 World Cup strategy heavily relies on spinners, with a focus on middle-order power through Shivam Dube. Captain Rohit Sharma emphasizes the importance of team balance and versatility in the squad selection process. While Ravindra Jadeja and Axar Patel are the left-arm spinning allrounders in the squad, Kuldeep Yadav and Yuzvendra Chahal are the two wrist spinners.
title: I wanted four tweakers in T20 World Cup squad: Rohit Sharma

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad won the match by one run against Rajasthan Royals in the Indian Premier League on Thursday, thanks to unbeaten performances by Nitish Kumar, Travis Head, and Heinrich Klaasen. Rajasthan Royals managed 200/7, after a missed full toss by Rovman Powell off Bhuvneshwar Kumar, which was resolved by an LBW decision.
title: 'Jumps of Joy': Jubilation in Hyd as SRH edge out RR - Watch

description: Chennai's Meenambakkam airport poses challenges for pilots with turbulence, wind shifts, and reduced lift during takeoff and landing. Safety measures include continuous seat belt sign usage and cargo load adjustments for fuel efficiency.
title: How hot weather affects flight landings and take-offs

description: A Raj Bhavan employee accused governor C V Ananda Bose of molestation in Kolkata, sparking legal consultations and political reactions. PM Modi visited Raj Bhavan before campaigning, and concerns about corruption and violence were raised.
title: Raj Bhavan staffer accuses West Bengal governor of molestation

description: Rohini Acharya faces Laloo Prasad Yadav challenge in Saran Lok Sabha seat. Yadav, RJP candidate, determined despite financial disparity. Labels like 'dharti pakad' do not deter him.
title: It's Lalu's daughter vs Laloo Prasad Yadav in Bihar's Saran

description: Siura Gopalpur in Ballia faces challenges like lack of power, healthcare, employment, and clean water. Despite VIP connections, the village plunges into darkness post-dusk, highlighting the neglect and struggles of its residents.
title: The ‘Nowhere People’: Trapped between districts & deprivation

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad won the IPL match against Rajasthan Royals, securing a one-run victory on Thursday. Bhuvneshwar Kumar returned figures of 3 for 41, while Travis Head and Nitish Kumar Reddy contributed to a 96-run stand off 47 deliveries. Heinrich Klaasen and Reddy helped Hyderabad surpass the 200-run mark for the fifth time in the tournament.
title: Narrowest win & most sixes: Records set in SRH vs RR thriller

description: Microsoft investigates VPN connection issues caused by Windows 11 security update KB5036893, impacting various Windows versions. Users with TPM certificate problems can seek help via Windows Get Help app or Business Support portal, but uninstalling the update may risk vulnerability.
title: Microsoft says its probing VPN issues with latest Windows 11 update

description: All-rounder Nitish Kumar Reddy showcased his batting prowess in a victory for Sunrisers Hyderabad against Rajasthan Royals, earning praise from cricketing pundits and teammates. Former India batter Mohammad Kaif and Irfan Pathan praised Reddy's shot-making ability, particularly against experienced bowlers like Yuzvendra Chahal, and his ability to reach highs with his shoulders.
title: 'Inka naam bahut sunenge aap': Ex-players laud Nitish Reddy

description: Byju's implements weekly revenue-based payments for sales staff due to cash shortage. Employees receive a percentage of generated revenue till at least May 21, with performance pressure and potential payout suspension for underperformance.
title: Byju's links pay of sales staff to weekly revenue

description: The US has accused Russia of using chemical weapons, including poison gas, “as a method of warfare” against Ukrainian forces, in violation of a global ban on the use of such weapons. The state department said in a statement on Wednesday that Russia had used chloropicrin, a “choking agent” widely used during World War I, as well as tear gas, against Ukrainian troops.
title: Russia using chemical weapons in Ukraine, says US; Kremlin denies

description: BJP has convinced the controversial current representative in Kaiserganj, Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh, to step aside in favor of his younger son, Karan, while also nominating UP minister Dinesh Pratap Singh again from the Nehru-Gandhi family stronghold of Rae Bareli. BJP has taken action against Brij Bhushan in order to address the criticism that it was lenient towards the six-time MP.
title: BJP drops Brij Bhushan, fields his son instead

description: BJP has convinced the controversial current representative in Kaiserganj, Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh, to step aside in favor of his younger son, Karan, while also nominating UP minister Dinesh Pratap Singh again from the Nehru-Gandhi family stronghold of Rae Bareli. BJP has taken action against Brij Bhushan in order to address the criticism that it was lenient towards the six-time MP.
title: BJP drops Brij Bhushan, fields his son instead

description: Citroen and Stellantis prioritize local EV production in India over seeking benefits under the EV policy. They face challenges of market competition and high customer expectations but aim to meet demands through continuous launch of new cars and features.
title: India big opportunity for growth: Citroen
